# Proposal

## What will (likely) be the title of your project?

Discounted Cash Flows in Python

## In just a sentence or two, summarize your project. (E.g., "A website that lets you buy and sell stocks.")

A program file that allows a user to plot a series of cash inflows and outflows over a period of time. 

## In a paragraph or more, detail your project. What will your software do? What features will it have? How will it be executed?

The program should allow the user to input a planning horizon, which is the time period in which cash flows will be inserted. Then the program should allow the user to input
the cash flow for each time increment of the planning horizon until it reaches the last time increment. Thereafter, the program should create a plot of the cash flows, which
will show arrows from a common axis indicating the magnitude and direction of the cash flow for each time increment. Alternatively, a user should be able to generate a similiar
cash flow if the user specifies other cash flow series, such as uniform (equal cash flows over time period) and geometric (cash flows that increase linearly over time). 
The output is simply the cash flow diagram of the inputted values over the planning horizon. However, outputs for the present worth or future worth of an entire series is
possible if a fixed interest rate is inputted at the beginning of the program. Variable interest rates exist, but its implementation is outside the scope of the project. 

The ideal case is that as the user inputs the cah flows for each increment, the program will update the plot of the cash flow diagram in real time. However, the easier setup
will be to have the user input all of the cash flows to be plotted and then have the program plot the entire cash flow diagram at once. 

